message.content: "cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR". The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for question answering, which are common topics in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses a knowledge graph (KG) to represent the meaning of text, which is a topic in the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also deals with information retrieval, as it aims to answer questions based on a given knowledge graph, which is a topic in the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
